"For almost a decade, the benefits of cloud have been praised by the IT industry. With the promise of greater business agility, scalability and cost reduction resonating strongly with both IT and business leaders, the cloud has transformed the way many organisations procure and consume IT services. No longer is it a question of ‘if’ organisations will move to the cloud, today the question is ‘what’ organisations will put in it. For almost a decade, the benefits of cloud computing have been praised by the IT industry. However, despite the clear benefits of the cloud, it is not without its challenges. The fast and drastically changing IT landscape is leaving some CIOs and their teams struggling to stay in control. Cloud-based identity and access management (IDaaS) is a logical evolution of existing IAM practices and helps to solve the ‘anywhere, anytime, from any device’ access challenge, explains Phil Turner of Okta."
